The paper proposes a method for incorporating task-agnostic dynamics priors into a deep reinforcement learning agent. The approach involves pre-training a frame predictor on physics videos, which suggests that the paper could belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper involves reinforcement learning (RL), which suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Robotics (cs.RO) categories. Finally, the paper deals with dynamics models, which suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
